<section id="day1">
    <h2>Day 1 Itinerary</h2>

    <h3>Morning - Depart from Burlington, NC</h3>
    <p>We’ll leave Burlington early at 8:00 AM for a scenic 3-hour drive to Asheville, NC.</p>
    <p><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Burlington,+NC/Asheville,+NC/" target="_blank">View Route on Google Maps</a></p>
    <!-- Image Placeholder -->
    <img src="your_scenic_drive_image.jpg" alt="Scenic Drive" class="image">

    <h3>11:00 AM - Check-in at West Asheville Airbnb</h3>
    <p>Arrive at our eco-friendly Airbnb in West Asheville. It's the perfect spot to relax and rejuvenate.</p>
    <!-- Airbnb Listing URL -->
    <!-- <p><a href="your_airbnb_listing_url" target="_blank">View Airbnb Listing</a></p> -->
    <!-- Image Placeholder -->
    <img src="your_airbnb_image.jpg" alt="Airbnb in West Asheville" class="image">

    <h3>12:00 PM - Brunch at Tupelo Honey Café</h3>
    <p>Head to Tupelo Honey Café for a Southern-inspired brunch in downtown Asheville.</p>
    <p><a href="https://tupelohoneycafe.com/" target="_blank">Tupelo Honey Café Website</a></p>
    <!-- Image Placeholder -->
    <img src="your_tupelo_honey_image.jpg" alt="Tupelo Honey Café" class="image">

    <h3>2:00 PM - Visit Looking Glass Falls</h3>
    <p>After brunch, we’ll take a 45-minute drive to Pisgah National Forest to see Looking Glass Falls, a stunning waterfall surrounded by fall colors.</p>
    <p><a href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/nfsnc/recarea/?recid=48186" target="_blank">Pisgah National Forest - Looking Glass Falls Info</a></p>
    <p><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Looking+Glass+Falls/" target="_blank">View on Google Maps</a></p>
    <!-- Image Placeholder -->
    <img src="your_looking_glass_falls_image.jpg" alt="Looking Glass Falls" class="image">

    <h3>4:45 PM - Return to Airbnb and Relax</h3>
    <p>We’ll drive back to the Airbnb to relax and recharge before dinner.</p>

    <h3>6:30 PM - Romantic Dinner</h3>
    <p>We’ll choose between three great dinner spots in Asheville:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="https://marketplace-restaurant.com/" target="_blank">The Market Place</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://posanarestaurant.com/" target="_blank">Posana</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://curatetapasbar.com/" target="_blank">Cúrate</a></li>
    </ul>
    <!-- Image Placeholder -->
    <img src="your_dinner_option_image.jpg" alt="Dinner Options" class="image">

    <h3>9:00 PM - Evening Stroll & Nightcap</h3>
    <p>End the evening with a stroll through Pack Square and a nightcap at Sovereign Remedies or Crow & Quill.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="https://sovereignremedies.com/" target="_blank">Sovereign Remedies</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://thecrowandquill.com/" target="_blank">Crow & Quill</a></li>
    </ul>
    <!-- Image Placeholder -->
    <img src="your_pack_square_image.jpg" alt="Pack Square" class="image">
</section>

<section id="day2">
    <h2>Day 2 Itinerary</h2>

    <h3>8:00 AM - Breakfast at Biltmore Village</h3>
    <p>We’ll start the day with a delicious breakfast at Well-Bred Bakery in Biltmore Village.</p>
    <p><a href="https://www.wellbredbakery.com/" target="_blank">Well-Bred Bakery</a></p>
    <!-- Image Placeholder -->
    <img src="your_biltmore_village_image.jpg" alt="Biltmore Village" class="image">

    <h3>9:30 AM - Scenic Drive & Hike at Craggy Gardens</h3>
    <p>After breakfast, we’ll take a scenic drive along the Blue Ridge Parkway to Craggy Gardens for a short hike with breathtaking mountain views and fall colors.</p>
    <p><a href="https://www.blueridgeparkway.org/poi/craggy-gardens/" target="_blank">Craggy Gardens Info</a></p>
    <!-- Image Placeholder -->
    <img src="your_craggy_gardens_image.jpg" alt="Craggy Gardens" class="image">

    <h3>12:00 PM - Drive Back to Burlington, NC</h3>
    <p>After our hike, we’ll begin the 3-hour drive back to Burlington.</p>
    <p><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Craggy+Gardens/Burlington,+NC/" target="_blank">View Route on Google Maps</a></p>
    <!-- Image Placeholder -->
    <img src="your_return_trip_image.jpg" alt="Return Trip" class="image">
</section>

